			<div class="medium-4 columns">
				<img src='img/mugshots/Jamo.jpg' width="100%" />
				<h5>James Elias</h5>
				<h6 class="subheader">Lead vocals</h6>
				<p>James started leading bands in the mid 1980s in the emerging punk
					rock scene. Later, while working at the legendary Little Bear in
					Evergreen, CO, he got to see artists like The Kinsey Report, Dave
					Mason, Buddy Guy, and Wayne Toups perform live in a small setting.
					In the 1990s, James fronted Furious George and the Monster Groove, an
					8-piece ska-funk powerhouse that was a regular in the front range
					music scene. He followed that up with Bad Rufus and The Ambassadors
					of Soul. Taking a break from touring bands, James fronted local bands
					The Pop Tarts and Band Gone Wild before starting up Edgewater
					Live.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="medium-4 columns">
				<img src='img/mugshots/John.jpg' width="100%" />
				<h5>John Gonzales</h5>
				<h6 class="subheader">Lead guitar</h6>
				<p>John has been playing in Denver for the last 20 years in multiple
					original bands including various music productions.  As a self-taught
					multi-instrumentalist he enjoys many styles of music.  The
					opportunity to play a variety of cover songs with the rest of
					Edgewater Live provided him with the challenge of learning more about
					music and having fun playing live.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="medium-4 columns">
				<img src='img/mugshots/Dewayne.jpg' width="100%" />
				<h5>DeWayne Even</h5>
				<h6 class="subheader">Rhythm guitar</h6>
				<p>A music educator, DeWayne played the trumpet through college and
					beyond, touring and performing extensively with a variety of
					world-class ensembles. He played trumpet in Savvy Backbone and The
					Redemptions before taking on the electric guitar. DeWayne loves music
					of all kinds, especially live music.</p> 
			</div>

		</div>

		<div class="row">

			<div class="medium-4 medium-offset-2 columns">
				<img src='img/mugshots/Peter.jpg' width="100%" />
				<h5>Peter Provost</h5>
				<h6 class="subheader">Bass</h6>
				<p>Computer engineer, hacker, gamer, musician and family man are all
					ways to describe Peter. He picked up his first guitar as a kid, and
					over the years taught himself banjo, ukulele, piano and bass guitar.
					Peter played guitar and keyboards in Denver bands Savvy Backbone and
					Harrison before taking a break from the music scene. Returning as the
					bass player for Edgewater live, his musical tastes cover everything
					from metal to reggae to hippie folk and classic rock.</p>
			</div>

			<div class="medium-4 columns end">
				<img src='img/mugshots/Brad.jpg' width="100%" />
				<h5>Brad Taylor</h5>
				<h6 class="subheader">Drums</h6>
				<p>Brad has provided his self-taught drum flair to many bands
					throughout Denver over the past 25 yrs, with the ability to mold into
					any genre - rock, alternative, country, blues, soul or reggae.  He
					has played relentlessly throughout the Denver music scene in original
					bands such as The Flipside, Crash Heroes, BLVD, and Boat Car, not
					only as drummer but also percussionist, singer and songwriter;  while
					also serving as a session drummer for many local artists.  Brad’s
					influences, as well as his musical tastes cover the entire musical
					gamut from big band to metal, classic rock to bluegrass.  As a family
					man and business professional, Edgewater Live has provided Brad the
					opportunity to once again find comfort in what he loves: Brad don’t
					wanna work, he just wanna bang on his drum all day.</p>
